## ğŸ” **4. How Azure Ensures Reliability**

| Concept               | Description                                                 | Real-World Analogy                                      |
| --------------------- | ----------------------------------------------------------- | ------------------------------------------------------- |
| **Availability Zone** | Protects against datacenter-level failures within a region. | Like having 3 separate power plants for one city.       |
| **Region Pair**       | Protects against region-wide disasters.                     | If one city loses power, another city provides backup.  |
| **Sovereign Region**  | Special isolated cloud for government use.                  | Like a private secure cloud just for national agencies. |

---

## âš¡ **5. Availability Zone Types of Services**

| Service Type       | What It Means                                         | Example                                         |
| ------------------ | ----------------------------------------------------- | ----------------------------------------------- |
| **Zonal**          | Resource tied to a specific AZ.                       | A VM created in Zone 1.                         |
| **Zone-Redundant** | Azure automatically replicates data across zones.     | Zone-Redundant Storage (ZRS).                   |
| **Non-Regional**   | Service runs globally without specific region choice. | Azure DNS, Traffic Manager, Microsoft Entra ID. |

---

## ğŸŒ **6. Region Pair Examples**

| Geography  | Region Pair                              | Distance (approx.)   | Special Note                   |
| ---------- | ---------------------------------------- | -------------------- | ------------------------------ |
| **US**     | East US â†” West US                        | 300+ miles           | Default US failover pair       |
| **Asia**   | Southeast Asia â†” East Asia               | 300+ miles           | For regional disaster recovery |
| **India**  | West India â†” South India â†” Central India | 300+ miles           | One-direction pairing          |
| **Brazil** | Brazil South â†” South Central US          | Cross-continent pair | Exception case                 |

